<task id="AIPU2-116" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Cross-matter privilege leakage test</title>
    <phase>6</phase>
    <tags>testing, security</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-028, AIPU2-027</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Legal workspace AI must never leak privileged document content across matter boundaries.
    This test suite verifies the privilege filter (AIPU2-028) and matter context isolation
    (AIPU2-027) work correctly under realistic cross-matter scenarios. The key risk: a user
    who has access to Matter A and Matter B could inadvertently (or deliberately) trigger the
    AI to reference Matter A documents when working in Matter B context. The design allows
    AI conclusions to persist in conversation history but must strip source document content.
  </prompt>
  <role>Security engineer focused on data isolation and privilege boundary enforcement.</role>
  <goal>
    No document content from Matter A is accessible when the active context is Matter B.
    Users are notified of the privilege boundary on matter pivot. AI conclusions from prior
    context are preserved in history but source document text is stripped. Unauthorized users
    cannot search or retrieve documents from a matter they do not have access to.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r2/design.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Authorization</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Set up test fixtures: two matters (Matter A and Matter B) with distinct documents. User has authorized access to both. Create sessions with document context loaded for each matter.</step>
    <step>Test 1 — Matter pivot content stripping: start with Matter A context (documents loaded), switch to Matter B, send a query that would elicit reference to Matter A documents. Verify the AI response contains no Matter A document text. Verify a privilege boundary notification appears in the UI.</step>
    <step>Test 2 — History preservation: after the Matter A -> Matter B pivot, verify that AI conclusions from the Matter A session appear in conversation history (e.g. "You previously found that...") but that the underlying source passages are not quoted or accessible.</step>
    <step>Test 3 — Cross-matter search: from Matter B context, attempt a search query that would match Matter A documents (by content similarity). Verify search results only return Matter B documents.</step>
    <step>Test 4 — Unauthorized user: create a test scenario where a user has access to Matter B but not Matter A. Attempt to access Matter A session data or documents. Verify 403 Forbidden is returned and no content is leaked.</step>
    <step>Test 5 — Forced injection: attempt to craft a chat message that references Matter A document IDs directly (e.g. "Summarize document ID abc123 from Matter A"). Verify the API rejects the request or returns empty content with an authorization error.</step>
    <step>Document all test cases, inputs, expected outcomes, and actual outcomes in notes/privilege-leakage-test-report.md.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Matter pivot: no Matter A document text appears in AI responses when active context is Matter B.</criterion>
    <criterion>Privilege boundary notification is shown to the user on matter pivot.</criterion>
    <criterion>AI conclusions from prior context are preserved in history; source document passages are not accessible.</criterion>
    <criterion>Cross-matter search returns only documents from the active matter.</criterion>
    <criterion>Unauthorized user receives 403 Forbidden when attempting to access a matter they do not have access to.</criterion>
    <criterion>Direct document ID reference from an unauthorized matter is rejected by the API.</criterion>
    <criterion>Test report written to notes/privilege-leakage-test-report.md with all 5 test cases documented.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
